Grillable Veggie Burger

1 c (155g) cooked brown rice
1c (120g) raw walnuts (or sub bread crumbs)
1/2 tbsp grape seed or avocado oil + more for cooking
1/2 white onion (~55g | 3/4 c) finely diced
1 tbsp (~8g) each chili powder, cumin powder, and smoked paprika
1/2 tsp each sea salt and black pepper + more for coating burgers
1 tbsp (12g) coconut sugar (or sub organic brown or muscovado sugar)
1 1/2 c (227g) cooked black beans well rinsed , drained and patted dry
1/3 c (22g) panko bread crumbs (if gluten free, use gluten free bread crumbs)
3-4 tbsp (51-68) vegan bbq sauce

Heat skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add walnuts and toast for 5-7 min, stirring frequently, until fragran and golden brown. Set aside to let cool. Keep the skillet over medium heat. Once hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil and onion. Season with a bit of salt and pepper and saute for 3-4 min, or until fragrant and soft, and transclucent. Remove from heat and set aside. Once walnuts are cooled, add to blender/food processor with chili powder, cumin, smoked paprika, salt, pepper, and coconut sugar and blend until a fine meal is achieved. Set aside. In a large mixing bowl, mash the drained black beans, leaving only a few whole beans. Next add cooked rice, walnut mixture, sauteed onion, panko bread crumbs, bbq sauce, and mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min, or until a moldable dough forms. If dry, add extra 1-2 tbsp bbq sauce. If too wet, add more bread crumbs. Taste and adjust seasonings as needed. For large burgers, divide into 5 patties (1/2 c size) or form 10 smaller burgers (1/4 c size). Cook for 3-4 min on each side either grill or in skillet.

